-- Bortenlaenger Leaving Munich Bourse for Deutsches Aktieninstitut
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2012-04-21T10:35:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-21/bortenlaenger-leaving-munich-bourse-for-deutsches-aktieninstitut.html
Christine Bortenlaenger will resign
from her post as chief executive officer of the Munich stock
exchange this summer to become the new head of the Deutsches
Aktieninstitut.  Bortenlaenger also is leaving her position as a member of
the management board of Bayerische Boerse AG, the company that
operates the Munich stock exchange, Deutsches Aktieninstitut and
Bayerische Boerse said today in separate e-mailed statements.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
